        "title":  "Conquest of Makkah",
        "description":  "Bloodless liberation and cleansing of the Kaaba (20 Ramadan). During the Conquest of Mecca, the Prophet Muhammad (صَلَّى ٱللّٰهُ عَلَيْهِ وَآلِهِ وَسَلَّمَ) entered the city in a display of mercy and triumph, where Ali ibn Abi Talib (كَرَّمَ اللهُ وَجْهَهُ الْكَرِيم) famously climbed onto the Prophet\u0027s shoulders to reach and destroy the idols within the Kaaba, permanently restoring it to the worship of one God.",
        "icon":  "🕋",
